# Portfolio project

## Stack

- React 19, TypeScript, Vite, **Ant Design**, **react-router-dom**
- Routes in `src/App/index.tsx`; pages under `src/pages/<PageName>/`; shared shell under `src/components/AppLayout/` (see Cursor rule for folder/file conventions).

## Package manager: pnpm

- This repo uses **pnpm** (`pnpm-lock.yaml` is source of truth). Version is pinned in `package.json` as `packageManager`.
- Prefer: `pnpm install`, `pnpm dev`, `pnpm build`, `pnpm lint`
- If `pnpm` is not on PATH (common on Windows):
  - **Option A:** Run **PowerShell as Administrator** once: `corepack enable`, then reopen the terminal and use `pnpm` normally.
  - **Option B (no admin):** `npx pnpm@10.33.0 install` and same pattern for other commands (or any matching `packageManager` version).
- `npm run dev` / `npm run build` still work because they call the same scripts; for lockfile consistency, install dependencies with pnpm when possible.

## D-ID video (dev note for agents only)

- On **localhost**, D-ID requires a **public** `source_url` (https, ending in `.jpg`/`.jpeg`/`.png`); it cannot fetch `localhost`.
- Dev default avatar URL comes from `getPortfolioAvatarSourceUrl()` in `src/lib/portfolioAssets.ts` (production site, e.g. `https://portfolio-fawn-three-56.vercel.app`, or imgbb via `HEADER_AVATAR_SRC`).
- **Do not** add UI copy on the portfolio explaining localhost vs production for D-ID; keep that context in Cursor rules only. Validation errors from the form/API may still surface briefly when the user submits a bad URL.

## About the Maker (user-authored copy)

- `src/components/AboutMe/consts.ts` is **hand-edited by the user** (`SECTION_TITLE`, `ABOUT_PARAGRAPHS`, `ABOUT_STATS`).
- **Do not change, revert, or “improve”** that copy unless the user explicitly asks.
- Keep About body text only in `consts.ts`; `AboutMe/index.tsx` imports it (no duplicate hardcoded paragraphs).

## Edits

- Match existing patterns (Ant Design layout, functional components, TypeScript types).
- Avoid unrelated refactors and unsolicited new markdown files.
